China on Wednesday expressed regrets over the planned measures by the United States to raise tariffs on imported Chinese products, saying escalating trade frictions is against the interests of the two peoples as well as people of the world."China deeply regrets this, and will be forced to take necessary countermeasures if the US side puts the tariff measures into effect," says a statement released Wednesday.The United States announced Wednesday that it would raise tariffs on 200 billion US dollars worth of Chinese goods from 10 percent to 25 percent as of May 10. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun